# =============================================================================
# Keymoji Environment Variables
# =============================================================================
# 
# This file contains all available environment variables for the Keymoji project.
# 
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local:
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#
# 2. Fill in your actual values in .env.local
#    (Never commit .env.local to Git - it's in .gitignore)
#
# 3. Restart your development server:
#    npm run dev
#
# IMPORTANT NOTES:
# - Variables prefixed with VITE_ are available in the frontend via import.meta.env.VITE_*
# - Variables without VITE_ prefix are only available in Webpack build process
# - .env.local has highest priority (overrides all other .env files)
# - For production: Set variables in Vercel Environment Variables
#
# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED: Apertus (Swiss LLM) - n8n Webhook Token
# =============================================================================
# 
# Token for authenticating with the Apertus n8n webhook.
# This is required if you want to use the Apertus AI provider.
#
# How to generate:
#   npm run generate:token:dev   # For development
#   npm run generate:token:prod  # For production
#
# How to use:
#   1. Generate token using the command above
#   2. Add token to .env.local as VITE_N8N_APERTUS_TOKEN
#   3. Add the same token to your n8n workflow "Set Expected Token" node
#   4. Restart your dev server
#
# For Production:
#   Set in Vercel → Project Settings → Environment Variables
#   Name: VITE_N8N_APERTUS_TOKEN
#   Environments: Production, Preview, Development
#
VITE_N8N_APERTUS_TOKEN=your_apertus_n8n_token_here

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: API URLs (Security: Do not expose in public repos)
# =============================================================================
# 
# These variables can override the default API URLs.
# IMPORTANT: Do not commit real URLs to public repositories.
#
# Default values are defined in src/config/api.js
# Uncomment and set only in .env.local (never commit):
#
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-api-url.com/api
# VITE_N8N_URL=https://your-n8n-instance.com/webhook

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: Development Server Configuration
# =============================================================================
# 
# Configure the local development server.
# These are only used when running 'npm run dev'.
#
# Default values:
#   PORT: 8080
#   HOST: localhost
#
# Uncomment and modify if needed:
# PORT=8080
# HOST=localhost
